<exercise checkit-seed="0034" checkit-slug="M4" checkit-title="Finding a matrix inverse">
  <statement>
    <p>Show how to find the inverse of the matrix <m>C= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
1 &amp; 1 &amp; 1 &amp; 3 \\
-3 &amp; -2 &amp; -4 &amp; -6 \\
-4 &amp; -1 &amp; -6 &amp; -5 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 2 &amp; -3
\end{array}\right] </m>.</p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>C^{-1}= \left[\begin{array}{cccc}
-32 &amp; -19 &amp; 6 &amp; -4 \\
-12 &amp; -8 &amp; 3 &amp; -1 \\
15 &amp; 9 &amp; -3 &amp; 2 \\
10 &amp; 6 &amp; -2 &amp; 1
\end{array}\right] </me>
  </answer>
</exercise>

